 extreme floods in central Europe (2003) Nature, 425, pp. 166-169. , NATUAS, 0028-0836, 10.1038/nature01928; Park, J.S., Jung, H.S., Kim, R.S., Oh, J.H., Modeling summer extreme rainfall over the Korean Peninsula using Wakeby distribution (2001) Int. J. Climatol., 21 (11), pp. 1371-1384. , IJCLEU, 0899-8418, 10.1002/joc.701; Poulin, A., Huard, D., Favre, A.-C., Pugin, S., Importance of tail dependence in bivariate frequency analysis (2007) J. Hydrol. Eng., 12 (4), pp. 394-403. , JHYEFF, 1084-0699, 10.1061/(ASCE)1084-0699(2007)12:4(394); Sha, W.Y., Li, K.R., Yin, S.M., Temporal and spatial features and trend prediction of waterlogging disasters along the coastal areas in Southern China (1997) J. Nat. Disasters, 6 (1), pp. 70-81. , ZZAXEF, 1004-4574, and (in Chinese); Shiau, J.T., Feng, S., Nadarajah, S., Assessment of hydrological droughts for the Yellow River, China using copulas (2007) Hydrol. Processes, 21 (16), pp. 2157-2163. , HYPRE3, 1099-1085, 10.1002/hyp.6400; Shiau, J.T., Modarres, R., Copula-based drought severity-duration-frequency analysis in Iran (2009) Meteorol. Appl., 16 (4), pp. 481-489. , 1350-4827, 10.1002/met.145; Wigley, T., Impact of extreme events (1985) Nature, 316, pp. 106-107. , NATUAS, 0028-0836; Statement on the status of global climate in 2003 (2003), World Meteorological Organization (WMO). WMO Publication No. 966, GenevaManual on low flow estimation and prediction (2009), World Meteorological Organization (WMO), WMO Publication No. 1029, Koblenz, GermanyWotling, G., Bouvier, C., Danloux, J., Fritsch, J.-M., Regionalization of extreme precipitation distribution using the principal components of the topographical environment (2000) J. Hydrol. (Amsterdam), 233 (1-4), pp. 86-101. , JHYDA7, 0022-1694, 10.1016/S0022-1694(00)00232-8; Zhang, L., Singh, V.P., Bivariate flood frequency analysis using the copula method (2006) J. Hydrol. Eng., 11 (2), pp. 150-164. , JHYEFF, 1084-0699, 10.1061/(ASCE)1084-0699(2006)11:2(150); Zhang, L., Singh, V.P., B